<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="78" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="78">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="78">Length. Male: 6.6-6.8 mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="78">
Anterior margin of crown with a dark brown patch extending around ocellus and variably onto disc and to posterior margin, with a medial small yellow spot, a small dark brown spot adjacent to basal angles of eyes (Fig. 5
<normalizedToken originalValue="A–B">A-B</normalizedToken>
). Face with pronounced brown markings (Fig. 5D). Pronotum with longitudinal bands variably coalescing, sordid orange brown (Fig. 5
<normalizedToken originalValue="A–B">A-B</normalizedToken>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="78">
Crown of nearly uniform length, 0.36
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as distance between eyes, 0.38
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as median length of pronotum (Fig. 5
<normalizedToken originalValue="A–B">A-B</normalizedToken>
).
</paragraph>
